Abuja (Sundiata Post) – President
Muhammadu Buhari has again reassured Nigerians that he would not let them down
in his second term in office. Buhari spoke at the
Presidential Villa while receiving the leadership of the Arewa Consultative
Forum (ACF), who paid him a congratulatory visit. According to him, he would
work harder in the next four years to address the challenges facing the
country. According to Buhari, “This
is my last lap, I will try to work harder. I assure you, I will not let you
down.” Chairman
of the ACF’s board of trustees, Alhaji Adamu Fika who led the delegation, said
the visit was to congratulate the president over his victory at the polls. By Yakubu Uba Yola - The Director, Field Operations of President Muhammadu Buhari Campaign Organisation,… By Hassana Yakubu Kaduna, - The Supreme Council for Sharia in Nigeria, on Thursday congratulated… By Lucy Osuizigbo and Clara Egbogota Lagos - The National Leader of the All Progressives…